{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "5d49b23c-d19e-4bd8-84d5-7762131552de",
    "name": "Restful Booker- CRUD Suite",
    "description": "A Postman collection that discovers and validates the full Restful Booker REST API by executing a complete booking lifecycle journey. The collection is designed to run repeatedly against any environment without manual intervention, demonstrating how the API endpoints chain together in a real-world usage sequence.\n\n### **Structure**\n\n**Auth**  \nHealth check to confirm the service is live, followed by token acquisition via POST /auth. The token is automatically captured from the response and stored as an environment variable, making it available to all subsequent authenticated requests without any manual copying.\n\n**Booking**  \nFull CRUD journey executed in sequence - Create → Read → List → Update (PUT) → Partial Update (PATCH) → Delete → Confirm Deletion. Each request passes its output forward as input to the next, forming a single replayable end-to-end journey.\n\n**Negative Tests**  \nValidates error handling for non-existent resources, confirming the API returns the correct HTTP 404 response for invalid booking IDs.\n\n### Key Features\n\n- **`{{baseUrl}}`** **parametrisation** - the entire collection runs against any environment (DEV, UAT, production) by switching the active Postman environment. No request URLs contain hardcoded values.\n    \n- **Random data generation** - every run generates a unique guest name and price using `Date.now()` and `Math.random()` in pre-request scripts. The collection can be executed back-to-back without data conflicts or stale state.\n    \n- **Automatic variable chaining** -`bookingId` and `token` are captured from responses and injected into subsequent requests automatically. The full CRUD journey runs from start to finish with zero manual intervention.\n    \n- **Clean run guarantee** - the Health Check pre-request script clears all environment and collection variables before each run, ensuring no residual state from a previous execution affects results.\n    \n- **26 test assertions across 9 requests** - every request validates its HTTP status code and key response body fields. The full suite passes with 0 failures.\n    \n\n### Test Coverage\n\n| Request | Method | Endpoint | Tests |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Health Check | GET | /ping | Service up, response time |\n| Get Auth Token | POST | /auth | Status 200, token exists, token stored |\n| Create Booking | POST | /booking | Status 200, ID stored, name/dates verified |\n| Get Booking | GET | /booking/{{bookingId}} | Status 200, all fields verified |\n| Update Booking | PUT | /booking/{{bookingId}} | Status 200, updated fields verified |\n| Partial Update | PATCH | /booking/{{bookingId}} | Status 200, patched field verified |\n| Delete Booking | DELETE | /booking/{{bookingId}} | Status 201 confirmed |\n| Verify Deletion | GET | /booking/{{bookingId}} | Status 404 confirmed |\n| Get Invalid Booking | GET | /booking/999999999 | Status 404 confirmed |\n\n### How to Run\n\n1. Import both files into Postman - the collection and the `restful-booker-DEV` environment file.\n    \n2. Select the **restful-booker-DEV** environment from the environment dropdown (top right).\n    \n3. Open the collection → click **Run collection**.\n    \n4. Ensure requests are in order and the correct environment is active → click **Run Restful Booker CRUD Suite**.\n    \n5. View results in the collection runner. A test run report is included in the submission showing 26 passed, 0 failed.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "54622148",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/54622148-5d49b23c-d19e-4bd8-84d5-7762131552de?source=collection_link"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Service is up - 201\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Response time is acceptable\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(3000);\r",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Clear BOTH environment AND collection variables for a guaranteed clean run",
                  "pm.environment.set(\"token\", \"\");",
                  "pm.environment.set(\"bookingId\", \"\");",
                  "pm.environment.set(\"firstName\", \"\");",
                  "pm.environment.set(\"lastName\", \"\");",
                  "pm.environment.set(\"totalPrice\", \"\");",
                  "pm.environment.set(\"updatedFirstName\", \"\");",
                  "pm.environment.set(\"updatedLastName\", \"\");",
                  "pm.environment.set(\"patchedFirstName\", \"\");",
                  "",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"token\", \"\");",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"bookingId\", \"\");",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"firstName\", \"\");",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"lastName\", \"\");",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"totalPrice\", \"\");",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"updatedFirstName\", \"\");",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"updatedLastName\", \"\");",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set(\"patchedFirstName\", \"\");",
                  "",
                  "console.log(\"All variables cleared - starting fresh run.\");"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "apikey"
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/ping",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "ping"
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Auth Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Token exists and is a string\", function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.token).to.be.a(\"string\");",
                  "    pm.expect(json.token).to.have.length.above(0);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Token stored in environment variable\", function () {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"token\", json.token);",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.environment.get(\"token\")).to.eql(json.token);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n  \"username\": \"admin\",\r\n  \"password\": \"password123\"\r\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "auth"
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        }
